            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-035-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 35:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted,
                            see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן
                                אֱלִיהוּ וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 35:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Elihu
                                da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Elihu da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv berdi Elihu da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Elihu da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-035-fn2" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                (<emph>fajdaly</emph>) <emph>bolurmen</emph>, written after Heb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: (<emph>fajda</emph>)<emph> etärmin</emph>. | QB:
                                (<emph>fajda</emph>)<emph> etärmin</emph>. | ADub.III.84:
                                <emph>bolurmen</emph>
                            <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            <emph>etermen</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                            <emph>fajdalandym</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-035-fn3" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>maḥtavlar</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">זְמִרֹות </foreign>
                            ‘songs’. | C: <emph>maḥtovlar</emph>. | QB: <emph>maḥtovlar</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>maḥtavlar</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>maḥtavlar</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-035-fn4" type="footnote">Another alternative translation
                            to <emph>maḥtavlar</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">זְמִרֹות </foreign>
                            ‘songs’, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: <emph>maḥtovlar</emph>. | QB: <emph>maḥtovlar</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>maḥtavlar</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>maḥtavlar</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-035-fn5" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>anda firjat etedirler da qaruv bermejdir</emph>, the
                            equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >זְמִרֹות </foreign>
                            ‘songs’, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’. | C: <emph>anda ferjat etärlär da ǯoɣap bermästir</emph>. | QB:
                                <emph>anda ferjat etärlär da ǯoɣap bermästir</emph>. | ADub.III.84:
                                <emph>anda firjat etediler da qaruv bermejdi</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>anda firjat et́adiĺar da qaruv bermijdir</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-035-fn6" type="footnote">A North-Western Karaim form, cf.
                            SWKar. <emph>ajtsan</emph> &amp;lt; MWKar. *<emph>ajtsaŋ </emph>&amp;gt;
                            MNWKar. <emph>ajtsaj</emph> &amp;gt; NWKar. <emph>ajtsej</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
